brief_summary.textblock:
      1. Implement a single-visit program (SVP) for cervix cancer prevention in clinics serving a
           multi-ethnic population of women;

        2. Set up an efficient system for interpretation of Pap smears for patients in the SVP that
           will minimize waiting time;

        3. Determine the follow-up rates and compare them between women assigned to the SVP and a
           usual care program (UCP);

        4. Determine satisfaction and compare it between women assigned to the SVP and the UCP;

        5. Determine the cost-effectiveness and compare it between the SVP and UCP
